    {
      "description": "A great legal claim means nothing without a way to enforce it. Look at how structured procedures turn abstract rights into reality.",
      "title": "The rules of the courtroom game"
    },
    {
      "description": "Lawyers spend months arguing over which judge or state gets to hear a case. See why the physical location of a lawsuit often decides who wins.",
      "title": "Where to sue and why it matters"
    },
    {
      "description": "The discovery process is a powerful legal tool that forces opponents to hand over private emails, texts, and internal documents before a trial even begins.",
